def create_sliding_windows(data, window_size):
    X = []
    for i in range(len(data) - window_size):
        X.append(data[i:i + window_size])
    return np.array(X)

window_size = 5

In [14]:
def build_autoencoder(input_shape):
    input_layer = Input(shape=(input_shape,))
    encoded = Dense(128, activation='relu')(input_layer)
    encoded = Dense(64, activation='relu')(encoded)
    encoded = Dense(32, activation='relu')(encoded)
    
    decoded = Dense(64, activation='relu')(encoded)
    decoded = Dense(128, activation='relu')(decoded)
    decoded = Dense(input_shape, activation='linear')(decoded)
    
    autoencoder = Model(input_layer, decoded)
    return autoencoder

autoencoder = build_autoencoder(input_shape)
autoencoder.compile(optimizer='adam', loss='mean_squared_error')

history = autoencoder.fit(X_train_flat, X_train_flat, 
                          validation_data=(X_val_flat, X_val_flat), 
                          epochs=50, batch_size=32, shuffle=True)

In [17]:
def calculate_reconstruction_error(original, predicted):
    return np.mean(np.power(original - predicted, 2), axis=1)
In [18]:
